      "writtenOn": "2019-07-09T11:10:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is it meaningless to have both -buildbundle\u003dcros and -downloadprivatebundles, even if we specify both public and private test cases? Or is it not possible to specify both test cases?\n\nThis is question rather than comment, but I think I don\u0027t understand how to tell tast to run tasts in private bundles.\nLooking at the https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromiumos/platform/tast/+/HEAD/docs/running_tests.md#basic-syntax, it seems -buildbundle\u003dcrosint is the way, but it is the way to run *fresh* tests.\nHow do we tell tast to run prebuilt private tests on dut?\nIf just omitting -buildbundle and have -downloadprivatebundles is the way to do it, I wonder how we avoid conflict of the test name with public ones.",
      "parentUuid": "21f040d9_e349015e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 121,
        "startChar": 52,
        "endLine": 121,
